                            <comment id="12948334" author="janstey" created="Wed, 13 Aug 2008 11:31:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to fix the issue.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix employs a technique similar to that of the pipeline processor to preserve the exchange type. Basically, in order for a type of Exchange to be propagated, it must override the newInstance method so the routing slip has a way to create a clean instance of it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12948463" author="njiang" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2008 07:49:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied patch with thanks to Jonathan.&lt;br/&gt;
